- autocategorize rules

## UI tweaks + account nicknames (2026-07-19)
- [x] Type pill moved under the date (desktop table + mobile card), transaction
      id dropped from the list display entirely (still shown on the edit
      page's own heading, just not in the list).
- [x] Category chip row: "+" hidden once a category is assigned; shows a
      dotted "Set category" button instead when nothing's assigned yet.
- [x] Bulk-actions bar "Assign Type" button was using variant="subtle",
      nearly invisible against the bar's light-blue background — switched to
      "primary" to match its siblings.
- [x] Sidebar made collapsible on desktop (Flux `collapsible` prop). Real bug
      found + fixed along the way: the app's nav uses flux:navlist.* (not
      flux:sidebar.item/group), which has zero collapsed-desktop awareness,
      AND Flux's compiled dist.css doesn't ship the collapse utility classes
      at all (apparently pruned unless Flux's own examples use them) — since
      vendor/ is gitignored, the app's own Tailwind build never scanned Flux's
      stubs to generate them either. Fixed with an `@source` directive in
      app.css pointing at vendor/livewire/flux/stubs. Navlist groups without
      an icon (Linked Accounts, Reports) now cleanly hide when collapsed
      instead of showing broken truncated text; the collapse toggle is forced
      always-visible instead of Flux's default hidden-until-hover.
- [x] Account nicknames: the `accounts.nickname` column already existed,
      unused. Added an editable field on the accounts management page and an
      `Account::display_name` accessor (nickname if set, else real name),
      applied everywhere an account name is shown to a user (transaction
      list, account filter/picker, sidebar nav, transaction edit form).
- [x] Transaction list page felt too crowded with filters+chart always
      visible — resolved: Chart and Filters are now two separate
      Details-styled collapsible sections (collapsed by default, same
      look as the existing "Details" box), so browsing "all transactions"
      starts lean but reaching for a filter or the chart is still one
      click away. Built with Alpine rather than native <details> — the
      native version's open/closed state doesn't survive a Livewire
      re-render (see below), so it kept snapping shut mid-use.
      Also fixed in the same pass: mobile card's date/type-pill/account
      now share one line; page-heading component no longer repeats the
      subheading as both a trailing breadcrumb crumb and the subheading
      line below (was showing key info twice on every page using
      breadcrumbs, not just this one).
- [ ] Discussed: how transfers to/from untracked accounts (e.g. a family
      member's private account) get handled — currently no automatic
      distinction between "this external transfer is really a gift/
      reimbursement" (should probably be income) vs "this is genuinely my
      own money, just moving to an account I don't track" (correctly stays
      a non-reportable transfer). Resolution for now: manual — use the
      Type field on the transaction edit page to reclassify a one-off as
      income/expense if that's what it really is; the category field is
      still available on transfer-typed transactions too, for tagging
      intent (e.g. "gift from mom") without affecting whether it counts in
      totals. No new mechanism built; revisit if manual reclassification
      turns out to be too common/tedious in practice.

