## Category suggestion heuristics + follow-up fixes (2026-07-18)
- [x] Added `suggestCategoriesForTransaction()`: up to two best-guess
      categories shown above the picker's list, fetched on-demand when
      the modal opens (not baked into page load, so it works for any
      transaction including ones already categorized). Two heuristics,
      deduped and capped at 2: (1) category most commonly assigned to
      other transactions from the same `merchant_name`; (2) falls back
      to the category most commonly assigned to transactions sharing
      the same `original_category_id` (Plaid's own categorization),
      for cases merchant_name is missing/inconsistent. Already-
      assigned categories are excluded. Neither heuristic is scoped to
      the current user — matches the existing (pre-session)
      `merchantSuggestions()` convention, since Category records are
      global/shared in this app, not per-user. 4 new Pest tests.
- [x] Suggestion buttons use the same neutral text/border styling as
      regular category-list rows (just the category-color dot to
      distinguish "this is a suggestion"), instead of a per-suggestion
      dynamic border/text color — and show a "Loading suggestions..."
      placeholder while the fetch is in flight.
- [x] Fixed: applying a suggested (or any) category showed the full
      list/card "loading blanket" even though the optimistic pill
      already gives instant feedback — the blanket's `wire:loading`
      was untargeted, so it fired for ANY component request including
      saveCategory/clearCategory/createCategory. Added a
      `loadingTarget` prop to `<x-responsive-table>` so it can be
      scoped (via `wire:target`) to just the page-reload-triggering
      properties (search/filters/pagination), leaving the fast
      optimistic actions silent.
- [x] Fixed: saving a suggested category was also auto-scrolling the
      page — turned out to be the pagination links' `scrollTo`
      option firing on any component re-render, not just actual page
      navigation. Disabled it (`scrollTo: false`).
- [x] Fixed: forcing the "Details" box always-expanded (no collapse)
      starting at `md:`/`lg:` broke iPad-landscape layouts — the
      two-column (filters | details) split was happening at the same
      breakpoint, and Tailwind's viewport-based breakpoints don't
      account for the app's own persistent sidebar eating into actual
      available width, so filters got squeezed into a sub-640px
      column and lost their side-by-side label+input layout. Fixed by
      splitting the two concerns: always-expanded starts at `lg:`
      (1024px, roughly iPad landscape) but STACKED full-width; the
      side-by-side layout with the filters only kicks in at `xl:`
      (1280px+), where there's actually room. Implemented via two
      separate containers (a `<details>` for below `lg:`, a plain
      always-visible div for `lg:` and up) sharing one Blade partial
      for the inner content, since CSS tricks to force a native
      `<details>` open via child `!important` overrides don't
      reliably override the browser's own layout sizing for the
      `<details>` element itself.

